2 Estimation

Binomial coefficient logfact . , \[\binom{n}{k} = \frac{n!}{k!(n-k)!}\] logfact(n) - logfact(k) - logfact(n-k) .

Planes.txt . PlanesJ.txt .

x <- 10 # number of captures
k <- 4  # number of recaptures from n
n <- 5  # size of second sample
tmax <- 50 # maximum population size
zeros <- 0 # for zeros trick

data <- list("x","k","n","tmax","zeros")

# Planes
mymodel <- function() {
  # Hypergeometric Likelihood Via Zeros Trick
  logterm1 <- logfact(x+.01)-logfact(k+.01)-logfact(x-k+.01)
  logterm2 <- logfact(t-x+.01)-logfact(n-k+.01)-logfact((t-x)-(n-k)+.01)
  logterm3 <- logfact(t+.01)-logfact(n+.01)-logfact(t-n+.01)
  C <- 1000
  phi <- -(logterm1+logterm2-logterm3)+C 
  zeros ~ dpois(phi)
  # Prior on Population Size
  for (i in 1:tmax){
    tptmp[i] <- step(i-(x+n-k))
    tp[i] <- tptmp[i]/sum(tptmp[1:tmax])
  }
  t ~ dcat(tp[])
  }

samples <- jags(data = data,
                parameters.to.save = c("t"),
                inits = list(list(t = 25)),
                model.file = mymodel,
                n.chains = 1, n.iter = 10000, n.burnin = 1, n.thin = 1,
                jags.module = c("dic")
)
